From fee4d949da89491f7c56e36fc44ed4ec438706cf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jarek Prokop <jprokop@redhat.com>
Date: Fri, 22 Sep 2023 15:59:52 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Also stop the HTTP parser in addition to resetting it.

The behavior was depending on an exception raised later after resetting the parser
and then this resulting in parser not calling any further callback.
With http_parser.rb >= 0.6.1 this is no longer true.

Stopping the parser at this point seems correct as it also stops firing
additional callbacks from being called.

Fixes failure in test suite:
```
Failure/Error: if !client.continue?
     NoMethodError:
       undefined method `continue?' for nil:NilClass
```
From `EventMachine::HttpRequest should close connection on invalid HTTP response'.
---
 lib/em-http/http_connection.rb | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/lib/em-http/http_connection.rb b/lib/em-http/http_connection.rb
index 755a042..d25c6d8 100644
--- a/lib/em-http/http_connection.rb
+++ b/lib/em-http/http_connection.rb
@@ -190,6 +190,7 @@ module EventMachine
           # the connection because we're processing invalid HTTP
           @p.reset!
           unbind
+          :stop
         end
       end
 
